HEADWORD: Sinaitic
<hw>Si`na*it"ic</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From Mount
<ets>Sinai</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Mount Sinai; given or
made at Mount Sinai; <as>as, the <ex>Sinaitic</ex> law</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sinaitic manuscript</b></col>, <cd>a fourth century Greek
manuscript of the part Bible, discovered at Mount Sinai (the greater
part of it in 1859) by Tisschendorf, a German Biblical critic; -- called
also <altname>Codex Sinaiticus</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinalbin</ent>⟦br⟧
